ho accidentally became a Mexican drug cartel queen]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132460875.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Chelsie Anderson went from serving tables to becoming a pivotal figure in drug trafficking. After her marriage fell apart, she linked up with a global cartel and quickly escalated within their ranks, overseeing substantial drug shipments each week. Eventually, she emerged as a key leader in an international drug ring, underscoring the intricate web of criminal operations and the people involved.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-chelsie-anderson-american-mom-of-two-who-accidentally-became-a-mexican-drug-cartel-queen/articleshow/132460875.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/meet-chelsie-anderson-american-mom-of-two-who-accidentally-became-a-mexican-drug-cartel-queen/articleshow/132460875.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T23:53:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132460893,imgsize-105970.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘This will offend a lot of people’: New UK PM Andy Burnham's tea-making habit sparks debate]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132467059.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/this-will-offend-a-lot-of-people-new-uk-pm-andy-burnhams-tea-making-habit-sparks-debate/articleshow/132467059.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/this-will-offend-a-lot-of-people-new-uk-pm-andy-burnhams-tea-making-habit-sparks-debate/articleshow/132467059.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T23:29:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132467064,imgsize-103336.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists studied pangolin DNA from seven countries and rediscovered a Himalayan species that had been overlooked since 1836]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132455874.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Brian Hodgson described a new pangolin species in Nepal during 1836. Modern genetic analysis of smuggled scales revealed a distinct lineage. This lineage matched Hodgson's forgotten description, confirming a separate species. Scientists have now officially recognized the Himalayan pangolin, Manis aurita. This discovery highlights the importance of historical observations and modern science.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-studied-pangolin-dna-from-seven-countries-and-rediscovered-a-himalayan-species-that-had-been-overlooked-since-1836/articleshow/132455874.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-studied-pangolin-dna-from-seven-countries-and-rediscovered-a-himalayan-species-that-had-been-overlooked-since-1836/articleshow/132455874.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T23:57:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132455990,imgsize-64883.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian immigrant Taranpreet Singh Sidhu found dead in Canada's Ontario]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132463737.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indian-immigrant-taranpreet-singh-s